..TEXT:
The 'stairs' to which Virgil refers are monstrous creatures, as
he looks ahead to their means of conveyance over the great gaps in
walkable terrain that they will face at Cocytus (^Inf~. XXXI.142-143,
Antaeus will be their 'stairs' then) and at the center of the Earth
(^Inf~. XXXIV.73-75, where Satan's legs will be the ladder Virgil
climbs to begin to draw Dante up from hell).
